The paper deals with a problem of distributed consensus in a sensor network, which involves communication and information processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with control and optimization aspects of the problem, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of sensor networks and communication protocols suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a novel quantization scheme, which involves computation and algorithms, suggesting the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper deals with numerical simulations and performance evaluation, suggesting the category cs.MA (Machine Learning).
